<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 7:14PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Dickenson
and southern Buchanan Counties through 745 PM EDT...
At 714 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Haysi, moving east at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Grundy, Haysi, Davenport, John Flannagan Lake, Clinchco, Stacy, Nora,
Vansant, McClure and Oakwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
